/OLID/OL6781929M-S.jpg','https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/OLID/OL6781929M-M.jpg'),(7233294,454,'Harper & Brothers','The law and the lady. A novel.','no description found','https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/OLID/OL24249599M-S.jpg','https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/OLID/OL24249599M-M.jpg'),(7241634,104,'Hodder & Stoughton','The angel of terror','no description found','https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/OLID/OL9627408M-S.jpg','https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/OLID/OL9627408M-M.jpg'),(7245993,288,'Sampson Low, Marston & Co.','Pride and Prejudice','Pride and Prejudice is an 1813 novel of manners written by Jane Austen. The novel follows the character development of Elizabeth Bennet, the dynamic protagonist of the book who learns about the repercussions of hasty judgments and comes to appreciate the difference between superficial goodness and actual goodness.\r\n\r\nMr. Bennet, owner of the Longbourn estate in Hertfordshire, has five daughters, but his property is entailed and can only be passed to a male heir. His wife also lacks an inheritance, so his family faces becoming very poor upon his death. Thus, it is imperative that at least one of the girls marry well to support the others, which is a motivation that drives the plot.','https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/OLID/OL37250029M-S.jpg','https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/OLID/OL37250029M-M.jpg'),(7251393,147,'B. Tauchnitz','The Secret Agent','Inspired by an actual attempt in 1894 to blow up London\'s Greenwich Observatory, here is a chillingly prophetic examination of contemporary terrorism-and the literary precursor to today\'s espionage thriller.','https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/OLID/OL2640257M-S.jpg','https://covers.openlibrary.org/b/OLID/OL2640257M-M.jpg'),(7353846,208,'Puffin','Five Children and It (Puffin Classics)','Haven\'t you ever thought what you would wish for if you were granted three wishes? In Nesbit\'s delightful classic, five siblings find a creature that grants their wishes, but as the old saying goes: be